# Docker reads THIS file (at the build-context root) — the build context for the
# backend image is the repo root (`docker build -f server/Dockerfile ... .`), so
# the ignore file must live here, NOT in server/. Without it Docker ships the
# whole 2.5 GB repo (dist, public assets, scrape, node_modules, .git) to the
# daemon and the build appears to hang on "transferring context".
#
# The backend bundle only needs: server/, src/ (the reused engine), shared/.
# Everything below is excluded from the context.

# Dependencies (reinstalled inside the image)
**/node_modules

# Build outputs / caches
dist
build
server/dist
.vite
*.tsbuildinfo

# Large frontend-only assets & data — the backend never needs these
public
incoming-assets
scrape
effect-coverage.csv
effect-coverage.md
effect-review-worklist.csv
test-results.txt

# VCS, history, editor, deploy metadata
.git
.gitignore
.history
.vercel
.vercelignore
.idea
.vscode

# Docs
docs

# Local env / secrets — never bake these into an image
.env
.env.*
**/.env
**/.env.*
